    <div xml:id="PN384">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>meṉpālā ṉuṭaṉaṇaii</l>
<l>vañcikōṭ ṭuṟaṅkunārai</l>
<l>yaṟaikarumpiṉ pūvaruntum</l>
<l>vaṉpālāṟ karuṅkālvarakiṉ</l>
<l><gap quantity="52" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l>vaṅkaṭ kuṟumuyal veruva vayala</l>
<l>karuṅkōṭ ṭiruppaip pūvuṟaik kuntu</l>
<l>viḻaviṉ ṟāyiṉu muḻavar maṇṭai</l>
<l>yiruṅkeṭiṟṟu micaiyoṭu pūṅkaḷ vaikuntu</l>
<l><gap quantity="39" reason="lost" unit="character"/> tuṇaiyēm peruma</l>
<l>nelleṉṉā poṉṉeṉṉā</l>
<l>kaṉaṟṟakkoṇṭa naṟaveṉṉā</l>
<l><gap quantity="17" reason="lost" unit="character"/> maṉaiyeṉṉā vavaipalavum</l>
<l>yāṉṟaṇṭavun tāṉṟaṇṭā</l>
<l>ṉiṇamperutta koḻuñcōṟṟiṭai</l>
<l>maṇṇāṇap pukaḻvēṭṭu</l>
<l>nīrnāṇa neyvaḻaṅkip</l>
<l>purantō ṉentai yāmalantolai<gap quantity="10" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l>yaṉṉōṉai yuṭaiyē meṉpa<gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"/>vaṟaṭ</l>
<l>kiyāṇṭu niṟka veḷḷi māṇṭa</l>
<l>vuṇṭa naṉkalam peytu nuṭakkavun</l>
<l>tiṉṟa naṇpa lūṉṟōṇṭavum</l>
<l>vanta vaika lallatu</l>
<l>ceṉṟa vellaic celavaṟi yēṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>In the soft soil, the egrets(?) that slumber,</l>
<l>huddling together on the branches of the mahua trees (1f.)</l>
<l>eat flowers of the hacked-off sugarcane.</l>
<l corresp="4">In the hard soil, with black-stalked millet </l>
<l corresp="5">…………………………………….. </l>
<l corresp="6">so that the pretty-eyed little hares are frightened in the neighbourhood, </l>
<l corresp="7">flowers drip from black-branched mahua trees. </l>
<l corresp="8">Even though there is a festival today, the bowls of the ploughmen </l>
<l corresp="9">contain flowery toddy along with a dish of big Keṭiṟu fish. </l>
<l corresp="10">……………………. We are companions, of great man. </l>
<l corresp="11">Not considering paddy, not considering gold, </l>
<l corresp="12">not considering hot things, not considering liquors </l>
<l corresp="13">…………. not considering the house, those many things, </l>
<l corresp="14">when I am eager [for them], he will not stint. </l>
<l corresp="15">Into the fat rice enriched with fat, </l>
<l corresp="16">wanting fame that puts to shame the earth, </l>
<l corresp="17">giving ghee that put to shame the water, </l>
<l corresp="18">our father is the one who protects [us]. After having suffered … </l>
<l corresp="19">we [now] possess one like him, they say. … </l>
<l corresp="20a-c">Let Venus stand wherever. </l>
<l corresp="23">Expect of the day that comes </l>
<l corresp="20d-21">[for us] to pour [and] wash the good vessels from which we eat glorious things </l>
<l corresp="22">and to dig out meat [pieces] from between [our] teeth that have eaten, </l>
<l corresp="24">we won’t know of going [away] to the extent we went. </l>
</lg>
